cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper deals with finding Nash equilibria in continuous games, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the existence of equilibria and their conditions, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory). The use of gradient descent-ascent and the study of dynamics over measure spaces suggest the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the method for training GANs, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the study of interacting gradient flow suggests the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
